HEADWORD: Bethabara wood
<hw>Beth*ab"a*ra wood`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
highly elastic wood, used for fishing rods, etc. The tree is unknown,
but it is thought to be East Indian.</def>⟦br⟧
